 (44,'Hotel Susung','106-7, Yonghak-ro, Suseong-gu, Daegu 42217 South Korea','Daegu is an interior basin city known as Korea\'s third capital and the capital of Korea\'s Southeast region. It\'s adjacent to Palgongsan Mountain and Apsan Mountain, as well as the Nakdonggang River flows peacefully through. Hotel Suseong can be found resting on the slopes of Beobisan Mountain in Suseong District of Southeast Daegu, an area sometimes regarded as the Gangnam of Daegu.    A palace situated among a heavy forest with a clear view of Suseong Lake and Daegu. It is the place also referred to as \"the blue house\" and \"the Alps of Daegu\", where late President Park Jeong-Hee led the nation from the ashes of war and into a long-term national policy, and also the place where the history of Korean hotels began during the era of poverty in Korea. The old Daegu Suseong Tourist Hotel possessed a brilliance and brightness that was even more than Sheraton Grande Walkerhill of Seoul, becoming the first in its class in 1963 and has since been reborn with a new name of Hotel Suseong beginning from July 1st, 2012, after its storied 50-year history.    The hotel, which had long been abandoned, has brought great changes that are comparable to any of Seoul\'s luxury hotels. Hotel Suseong, with a passionate fire in its heart and spirit dynamically spreading its wings from the silent land ; Hotel Suseong, combining tradition with modern sensibilities, showing the grandeur of the Alps and the captivating appearance like the Salzburg; Hotel Suseong leading the generation of all-inclusive hotel facilities , with culture, art, performances, ceremonies, food, education, and accommodation; Hotel Suseong, incomparable with numerous other hotels surrounded by different pollutants of the city ; it is a resting place and haven in the middle of the city with various complex and dynamic stories.    Hotel Suseong will become the great stage for the coexistence of nature and humanity. We will develop it into the place of promises and meet-ups for global citizens on its sprawling 450,000-sq.ft space. We will fill it with humanity and make it an origin of fun lifestyles.    We will reclaim the reputation of being Korea\'s best hotel, which ushered in a Renaissance era for hotels, over half a century ago. We will listen and carefully reflect on the feedback and advice of our guests.    Lastly, we will put forward our very best and continued efforts to treat each and every guest as a VIP with differentiated and high-end products and services.','4.0','6/85','25','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/07/38/32/de/exterior.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','230.523 krw','Daegu','South Korea','Hotel','kr'),
