 (147,'Delicacy Central Hotel & Spa','61 Hang Be Hoan Kiem, Hanoi 100000 Vietnam','Warm welcome to Delicacy Central Hotel & Spa! Conveniently located on the busy Hang Be street – the heart of Hanoi city with walking distance to various popular tourism destinations. The 50 spacious rooms are designed with a contemporary outlook and furnished with five-star standard of amenities to bring a memorable and comfortable stay for the guests.','5.0','14/1035','361','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/18/94/2a/cc/central-sky-bar.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','63.519 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (148,'Hanoi Marvellous Hotel & Spa','55 Duong Thanh Street, Hanoi 10000 Vietnam','Your new home in Old Quarter of Hanoi. Top notch of the creation focused on needs and demands of guests. Hanoi Marvellous Hotel & Spa blends classic and elegances with modern style providing exquisite environment to every upscale single, couple, group, family for leisure or business travel in the heart of Hanoi Old Quarter. This brand new building established in January 2016 with 50 rooms & suites, restaurant, spa center as well as desk to information of travel in order to satisfy each 24 hour on your vacation. All rooms with large window, city view, balcony are strong points when bring natural light inside. Guests will appreciate our stylish accommodations. All 50 elegant rooms on 8th floors including connecting room type and 24 suites are with cozy duvet sleep system, seating area, desk, Internet TV system,... Spa center will relax you with traditional Vietnamese massage, Aroma therapy, Herbal steam bath, warm stone, foot recover massage,... Marvellous restaurant meets choices of vegetarian, vegan with featured menu. Also, it serves Vietnamese cuisine to all food lovers. Sky view space on the 6 floor will be an ideal for you to enjoy Panorama of the Old Quarter as well. Friendly, well experienced, enthusiastic, easy going and young team is our pride, too. We work for your satisfaction, for your carefree touch and cozy vacation. Hanoi Marvellous hotel - your home away from home - welcomes you!','5.0','15/1035','2173','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/15/a9/cd/7b/lobby.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','44.898 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (149,'Essence Palace Hotel & Spa','No. 27-29, Gia Ngu Street, Hoan Kiem District, Hanoi 100000 Vietnam','Ideally located in the heart of Hanoi’s Old Quarter, near the Lake of Sword Restored, the 4 star boutique Essence Palace hotel & spa offers you 30 luxurious guest rooms ranging from spacious balcony rooms for 1 – 3 people, to connecting rooms perfectly for a bigger family who opt to stay together but still have privacy. The famous cosy indoor Gia Ngu restaurant will delight you not only for daily breakfast but also offer great Vietnamese specialties for lunch and dinner. Our capable travel desk can arrange visa on arrival, tours of the city, Halong Bay cruises and trips to Hoi An or Sapa. Shopping lovers can spend their time in our Kitonali or Heydi tailoring boutique shops and later indulge in the Essencia Spa, which helps rejuvenate their bodies after a day of shopping or sightseeing.','5.0','16/1035','685','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/06/97/39/de/essence-palace-hotel.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','45.989 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (150,'Shining Boutique Hotel & Spa','71 Hang Bong Street Hoan Kiem District, Hanoi Vietnam\r\n','No descriptions','5.0','18/1035','317','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/15/d8/8c/f4/shining-boutique-hotel.jpg?w=300&h=300&s=1','42.281 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (151,'Hanoi Emerald Waters Hotel & Spa','47 Lo Su Hoan Kiem, Hanoi 100000 Vietnam','The Golden Sun Group introduces its crown jewel, the Hanoi Emerald Waters Hotel & Spa. Our latest hotel embodies the comfort of home and the luxury of a palace. The amenities include the Salmon Run restaurant, the Nexus Cafe, a rooftop fitness center and 50 premier rooms including families and suites. The hotel sits along the Hoan Kiem Lake just a few steps away from major attractions, shopping, the night - weekend market and historical landmarks. Our restaurants, the Salmon Run and the Nexus Cafe, are conveniently located on the 2nd floor. They provide the freshest seafood, authentic Vietnamese cuisine and Western favorites. The added touches of 24 hour customer service, daily turn down service, and free high speed WI-Fi, flat screen TV with cable and DVD will ensure a memorable stay. Upon your arrival , you will be pampered by our welcoming service and treated to sumptuous delights. We really look forward to serving you here at our Hanoi Emerald Waters Hotel soon. Yours sincerely','5.0','21/1035','923','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/11/92/8d/18/lobby--v17859197.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','30.612 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (152,'Hanoi Brilliant Hotel & Spa','44 Hang Trong Hoan Kiem, Hanoi 10000 Vietnam','Hanoi Brilliant Hotel & Spa epitomes the romance of the Old Quarter - an intoxicating blend of luxury, history and modern that no other hotels can match. Located in the majestic streets, ancient and popular with a wide range of luxury hotels and famous boutique craft, silk shops of Hanoi. The location is on 44 Hang Trong Str, Hoan Kiem, Hanoi.','5.0','25/1035','642','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/16/72/e1/a9/hanoi-brilliant-hotel.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','62.964 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (153,'Hai Bay Hotel','27 Hang Bong Hoan Kiem, Hanoi 100000 Vietnam','Everyone needs a place to lay their weary head. For travelers visiting Hanoi, Hai Bay Hotel is an excellent choice for rest and rejuvenation. Well-known for its romantic environment and proximity to great restaurants and attractions, Hai Bay Hotel makes it easy to enjoy the best of Hanoi.\r\n\r\nFree wifi is offered to guests, and rooms at Hai Bay Hotel offer air conditioning, a refrigerator, and a minibar.\r\n\r\nDuring your stay, take advantage of some of the amenities offered, including room service and a concierge. Guests of Hai Bay Hotel are also welcome to enjoy free breakfast, located on site.\r\n\r\nNearby landmarks such as St. Joseph\'s Cathedral (0.1 mi) and Imperial Citadel of Thang Long (0.6 mi) make Hai Bay Hotel a great place to stay when visiting Hanoi.\r\n\r\nWhen you’re feeling hungry, be sure to check out Kaiba, Makoto Restaurant, and Azuma Japanese Restaurant, which are some sushi restaurants that are popular with locals and out-of-towners alike.\r\n\r\nDuring your visit, be sure to check out popular attractions like Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum (0.9 mi), Old Quarter (0.5 mi), and Hoa Lo Prison (0.4 mi), which are all within walking distance of the hotel.\r\n\r\nWhether you’re traveling for business, pleasure or both, Hai Bay Hotel is sure to make your visit to Hanoi one worth remembering.','5.0','31/1035','767','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/14/30/da/2e/hai-bay-hotel.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','77.733 krw','Hanoi','Vietnam','Hotel','vn'),
 (154,'Cloud Nine Restaurant','27 Hang Be La Siesta Premium Hang Be, Old Quarter, Hoan Kiem, Hanoi 100000 Vietnam','To be on Cloud Nine is to be in a blissful state of happiness. A number of conflicting theories abound as to the origins of this phrase. One of the most popular attributes it to the fluffy white cumulonimbus. This is the ninth cloud out of ten types first identified in the 1896 International Cloud Atlas which rises as high as a cloud can go, hence the sense of being ‘on top of the world’.','5.0','9/2345','241','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/19/43/2e/b5/cloud-nine-restaurant.jpg','0','Hanoi','Vietnam','Restaurants','vn'),
 (155,'Lighthouse Sky Bar & Restaurant','27 Hang Be Rooftop, La Siesta Premium Hang Be, Hoan Kiem, Hanoi 100000 Vietnam','This ambitiously structured bar (unique to Hanoi and Vietnam for that matter) is styled on a boat which creatively plays to the meaning of Hang Be street. The bar is ‘moored’ over three levels of terrace space (Rooftop floors); its bow with the bar area overlooks the street while at the back the stern faces the Red River.','5.0','14/2345','179','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/19/eb/57/49/lighthouse-sky-bar-in.jpg','0','Hanoi','Vietnam','Restaurants','vn');
