 (251,'Half-Day Korean DMZ Tour from Seoul','Hongik Univ. Station, Donggyo-dong, Seoul, South Korea','Travelers that want to uncover the history of the Korean War may be disappointed to learn that independent travelers can\'t visit the demilitarized zone (DMZ) between North and South Korea. But with this guided tour, you can explore this storied area on the Korean border. Highlights include stops at the 3rd Tunnel and DMZ Exhibition Hall, views of the Freedom Bridge, and your guide\'s commentary on the history of the Korean War.','4.5','12/567','494','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/1a/61/33/d6/caption.jpg','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (252,'Korean Cooking Class with Full-Course Meal & Local Market Tour','377-3 Mangwon 1(il)-dong, Mapo-gu, Seoul, South Korea','Immerse yourself in Korean culture and enjoy an authentic home-cooking experience with a local chef at her home. Enjoy a guided visit to the local market to purchase fresh ingredients, sample tasty street food snacks, and learn about typical herbs and spices. Then, get hands-on as you create a selection of popular Korean dishes and master traditional cooking techniques. Finally sit down to enjoy a ‘Hanjeongsik’ dinner including your homemade dishes, along with additional side dishes and dessert.','5.0','13/567','137','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/1a/56/f4/97/caption.jpg','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (253,'Absolute: Seoul Pub Crawl & Party','407-26 Seogyo-dong, Mapo-gu, Seoul, South Korea','If you want to experience the wild side of Seoul\'s nightlife scene, look no further than this pub crawl and party tour. Perfect for solo travelers or large groups, this high-octane experience reveals the best of Seoul\'s bars and includes admission to 10 nightclubs and multiple discounts on drinks throughout the evening. Plus, three free shots are included.','5.0','14/567','103','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/1a/5c/dc/d9/caption.jpg','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (254,'Hiking to Bukhansan Peak(Baegundae: 836.5m) with Mountain Expert','262, Bogungmun-ro, Seongbuk-gu, Seoul 02700 South Korea','It’s a rare yet remarkable feat when you can explore a national park without even leaving the city you’re staying in. Escape Seoul for the day without having to spend hours traveling on a private hiking tour of Bukhansan National Park, designed with mountain climbing enthusiasts in mind. An expert mountain guide ensures your safety and confidence throughout the tour and tailors the route according to your fitness level and personal preference.','5.0','15/567','26','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/1a/8f/69/2b/caption.jpg','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (281,'Gyeongbokgung Palace','161 Sajik-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul South Korea','The National Museum of Korea and the National Folk Museum are located on the grounds of this palace, built six centuries ago by the founder of the Chosun dynasty.','4.5','6/974','10646','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/fc/e0/5e/gyeonghoeru.jpg?w=600&h=-1&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (282,'Myeongdong Shopping Street','Jung-gu, Seoul South Korea','The beauty shops such as Innisfree, Nature Republic and Olive Young is worth a visit as they might have special offers especially if you buy more.','4.5','30/974','10355','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/c2/a2/e0/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (283,'Changdeokgung Palace','99, Yulgok-ro, Jongno-gu, Seoul 03072 South Korea','This 600-year-old UNESCO World Heritage Site is the city\'s jewel. It\'s as famous for its outstanding architectural details as for its verdant and expansive gardens.','4.5','8/974','4611','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/02/57/75/4a/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (284,'The War Memorial of Korea','29, Itaewon-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul 04353 South Korea','Poignant exhibits, war memorabilia, art works, and military equipment make this a perfect place to learn about Korea’s history of war, most notably with North Korea. Kids will enjoy the display of actual tanks and airplanes.','4.5','3/974','4273','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/05/3c/83/32/the-war-memorial-of-korea.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (285,'National Museum of Korea','137 Seobinggo-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul 04383 South Korea','This is the largest museum in Korea with over 220,000 objects in its collection. It has six permanent exhibition galleries such as Historical Gallery and Fine Arts Gallery. It also has special exhibition halls, a children\'s museum, outdoor exhibit areas, restaurants, cafes, shops and other amenities. *Admission: Free to Permanent Exhibition & Children\'s Museum(changeable after 2010)*Hours: Tue/Thu/Fri: 9am-6pm, Wed/Sat: 9am-9pm, Sun/holidays: 9am-7pm, closed Mon & January 1st','4.5','5/974','2362','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/85/26/c7/front-view-of-the-national.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (286,'Insadong','Insa-dong, Jongno-gu, Seoul South Korea','Though touristy, this vibrant neighborhood is one of the cultural and artistic hubs of Seoul. Great tea houses, restaurants, street food, galleries and souvenir shops make it a must-see area.','4.0','37/974','6413','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/01/f0/8f/26/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (287,'Trickeye Museum Seoul','20, Hongik-ro 3-gil, Mapo-gu Seogyo Plaza B2, Seoul 04039 South Korea','The Trickeye Museum is \"one of a kind\" painting gallery, which combines art with hi-end technology - so-called AR (Augmented Reality) effect and 2D/3D illusions. Instead of merely viewing paintings (as in a typical art gallery), visitors can interact with the paintings using newly developed Trickeye Camera application to make pictures alive in order to be a part of the artwork and record it on video or make a picture. Moreover, there is the Ice Museum located in the Trickeye Museum, items in which are fully made out of ice such as iced TV, ice kitchen, ice slope etc. With one admission ticket you can enjoy both \"Trickeye Museum\" and \"Ice Museum\". To ensure that even its busiest customers have time to enjoy the fun, the museum stays open each day all around the year from 9 AM until 9 PM (last admission by 8 PM), making it a popular date and hang-out place. Outside of the main exhibition hall there is museum café, which exclusively serves Latte with Your picture from the phone on it.','4.5','23/974','1530','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/12/5e/cd/13/be-creative-with-ar-effect.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (288,'Lotte World Tower & Mall','300, Olympic-ro, Songpa-gu 117-123F, Lotte World Tower, Seoul 05551 South Korea','Lotte World Tower & Mall offers stores, cafes, restaurants, galleries, and even a concert hall. The Tower is the fifth highest in the world and has an observation deck, a skywalk, and a luxury hotel.','4.5','20/974','802','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0e/f3/03/2c/event-for-1st-day-of.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (289,'KTX (Korea Train Express)','Seoul South Korea','I find high speed train travel in Korea much more convenient than domestic flight as it saves you from heading to airport and clearing security etc.','4.5','14/974','1086','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/15/c0/35/2c/ktx.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (290,'Seoul Metro','Seoul South Korea','The exceptions—the times when a public transportation system actually IS an attraction—are pretty obvious: San Francisco’s cable cars, Valparaiso’s ascensors, Taipei’s Maogong Gondola, Innsbruck’s Nordkettenbahnen','4.5','1/974','12706','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/02/1b/7a/29/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (291,'Hangang Park','Seoul South Korea','This park is a good place to get away from the crowds and bustle of Seoul. The cycling trails (bikes are available for rent) are popular as are the swan boat rides. And the views of the Han river and city are stunning.','4.5','10/974','1570','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/f9/33/b0/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (292,'N Seoul Tower','105, Namsangongwon-gil, Yongsan-gu, Seoul 04340 South Korea','Built on a 262 meter peak in Namsan Park, the tower reaches to 480 meters above sea level. When the weather and pollution levels cooperate, visiting the observation tower (370 meters above sea level) allows you to view the entire city and surrounding areas.','4.0','41/974','9452','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/02/1f/d3/4c/caption.jpg?w=200&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (293,'Namsan Park','100-177 Hoehyeon-dong 1-ga, Jung-gu Yongsan-dong, Yongsan-gu, Seoul South Korea','Fantastic views of the city with the added bonus of the tower, cable car and locks affixed to the railings which made a fun scene.','4.5','24/974','2214','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/51/95/25/namsan-park.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (294,'Myeongdong NANTA Theater','26, Myeongdong-gil, Jung-gu UNESCO Hall 3F, Seoul 04536 South Korea','No descriptions','4.5','4/974','519','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/09/8f/2e/04/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Seoul','South Korea','Attractions','kr'),
 (295,'Concorde Hotel Singapore','100 Orchard Road Concorde Hotel And Shopping Mall, Singapore 238840 Singapore','An internationally renowned business hotel in Singapore. Strategically & conveniently located on Orchard Road, Concorde Hotel Singapore is just minutes away from places of interests such as Suntec City, Gardens by the Bay & Chinatown. Recently revamped; the hotel’s 407 rooms & suites have been thoughtfully designed to meet business & leisure travellers’ needs. All guestrooms are equipped with work areas & other modern amenities including Free Wi-Fi connectivity to ensure guests a comfortable stay. For unforgettable dining experiences, embark on a gastronomic journey, where the extensive menus will spoil diners with a wide variety & interesting mix of Local & Western cuisine. Be it a seminar, banquet, workshop, gala dinner, birthday, wedding, family reunion, dinner & dance or a business meeting, we can offer unparalleled meeting and event facilities catered to your requests. Just 5 mins away from Dhoby Ghaut & Somerset MRT stations, & 25 mins away from Changi Airport by car or taxi.','4.0','31/356','4520','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/45/08/2d/exterior.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','175.173 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (296,'Marina Bay Sands','10 Bayfront Avenue, Singapore 018956 Singapore','Located along Marina Bay waterfront with 3 cascading hotel towers, 2,560 rooms, extraordinary Sands Sky Park, floating crystal pavilions, lotus-inspired ArtScience Museum, The Shoppes, Celebrity Chef Restaurants, Theatres and hottest nightclubs.','4.5','56/356','29120','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/45/21/5d/lounge.jpg?w=300&h=300&s=1','396.082 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (297,'Capella Singapore','1 The Knolls, Sentosa Island 098297 Singapore','An ultra-luxury resort situated on Sentosa Island, Capella Singapore transports guests into a setting of ultimate peace and tranquility. Guests can enjoy its onsite, award-winning Auriga spa, three restaurants, as well as the beautiful landscape overlooking the South China Sea. Nearby facilities include a golf course, family and kids-friendly attractions. The hotel is also 10-15 minutes drive away from Singapore\'s bustling business and shopping districts.','4.5','2/17','2179','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/45/1c/49/exterior.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','571.768 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (298,'Hotel Jen Orchardgateway Singapore by Shangri-La','277 Orchard Road, Singapore 238858 Singapore','With elevated views of the city and situated right in the heart of Orchard Road, lies Hotel Jen Orchardgateway Singapore by Shangri-La. With so much to see, eat, shop and do, explore the Lion City at ease with unmatched, direct connectivity to public transport and a wide array of shopping and entertainment options right at your doorstep. Enthusiastic, upbeat and fuss-free service, thoughtfully equipped rooms and an award-winning rooftop infinity-edged pool await. An urban oasis above the pulsating city, soak up stunning panoramic views of the city skyline while lounging on the viewing platforms. Hotel Jen Orchardgateway Singapore is an SG Clean certified establishment with hygiene and sanitation measures inspected by Singapore Tourism Board’s appointed assessors.','4.5','42/356','2938','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/13/be/1d/4b/baywatch-jen-award-winning.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','123.997 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (299,'The St. Regis Singapore','29 Tanglin Road Orchard, Singapore 247911 Singapore\r\n','Situated at the heart of the city’s premier shopping district, with the world-class shopping of Orchard Road at your doorstep and the grandeurs of a 5-star hotel within, The St. Regis Singapore is the ideal residence for the discerning luxury traveller. The St. Regis experience begins when you arrive at Changi Airport. A luxurious St. Regis Bentley and chauffeur can be arranged for your journey to the address where timeless elegance resides.From its location at the most coveted address, set at the crossroads of the embassy district and the UNESCO World Heritage Site of Singapore Botanic Gardens, to the legendary St. Regis Butler Service, this is world-class hospitality at its finest.','4.5','58/356','2818','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/17/8c/54/eb/lobby.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','241.619 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (300,'W Singapore - Sentosa Cove','21 Ocean Way, Sentosa Island 098374 Singapore','Set on a resort island with sparkling sea views, W Singapore - Sentosa Cove is Asia\'s new tropical playground and the perfect destination to sip, play and flirt. An oasis of modern luxury for discerning business travellers, vivacious staycationers and sophisticated globetrotters.','4.5','7/17','2669','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1a/c2/09/e4/w-singapore-sentosa-cove.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','404.937 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (301,'The Fullerton Hotel Singapore','1 Fullerton Square, Singapore 049178 Singapore\r\n','Transformed from the Fullerton Building which was built in 1928, The Fullerton Hotel Singapore has been gazetted as Singapore\'s 71st National Monument. This luxury hotel features 400 elegant rooms and suites with views of the sunlit atrium, city, Singapore River or Marina Bay. Just 25 minutes from the airport, The Fullerton Hotel Singapore is located in the financial and arts districts, within walking distance to the National Gallery and minutes from the city\'s main shopping belt. The hotel features award-winning restaurants, the stylish Post Bar, an outdoor infinity pool, a 24-hour fitness centre and a luxury spa. We are honoured to be recognised as one of the Top 1 Percent of Hotels in Singapore by TripAdvisor Traveller\'s Choice Awards 2017.','4.5','1/356','7338','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/18/4a/d7/03/hotel.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','353.505 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (302,'Sofitel Singapore Sentosa Resort & Spa','2 Bukit Manis Road, Sentosa Island 099891 Singapore\r\n','Sofitel Singapore Sentosa Resort & Spa is the newest French luxury 5-star resort hotel on Singapore\'s favourite island. Situated at the top of a cliff rising above Tanjong Beach, it is a haven of tranquility and relaxation blessed with stunning views of sunsets over the horizon. Greeting guests upon arrival in the lobby is a dazzling bespoke lighting installation inspired by the Milky Way hanging from the lofty ceiling. The entire property is cosseted in lush tropical greenery and overlooks the South China Sea. The 215-room hotel includes luxury rooms, suites and villas, and offers an array of delectable cuisines from around the world at its various F&B establishments. Facilities include indoor and outdoor event spaces, a state-of-the-art gym, children\'s playroom, complimentary internet access and shuttle services. Completing the experience for guests is a spacious swimming pool deck and the world\'s largest Sofitel Signature So SPA.','4.5','4/17','3021','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0f/12/8d/84/sofitel-singapore-sentosa.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','284.162 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (303,'Siloso Beach Resort Sentosa','51 Imbiah Walk, Sentosa Island 099538 Singapore','Rooms at Siloso Beach Resort Sentosa Hotel provide a flat screen TV, air conditioning, and a refrigerator, and guests can stay connected with internet access.\r\n\r\nIn addition, while staying at Siloso Beach Hotel guests have access to a 24 hour front desk, room service, and a rooftop terrace. You can also enjoy a pool and free breakfast. Need a place to park? Free parking is available at Siloso Beach Hotel.\r\n\r\nFor those interested in checking out popular landmarks while visiting Sentosa Island, Siloso Beach Hotel is located a short distance from Sentosa Merlion (0.2 mi) and Tiger Sky Tower (0.2 mi).\r\n\r\nWhile in Sentosa Island be sure to experience local tapas favorites at The Knolls, FOC Sentosa, or LeBar.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in exploring Sentosa Island, check out a natural history museum, such as Sentosa Nature Discovery.\r\n\r\nSiloso Beach Resort Sentosa puts the best of Sentosa Island at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.','3.0','16/17','1645','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/07/96/04/60/pool--v5943473.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','228.360 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg');
