 (304,'Four Seasons Hotel Singapore','190 Orchard Boulevard, Singapore 248646 Singapore','Located on tranquil tree-lined Orchard Boulevard, the Four Seasons Hotel Singapore provides exclusive and understated luxury while being in the midst of the shopping and entertainment district of Orchard Road. Our 6000sqm 3rd floor Club houses 2 indoor air-conditioned tennis courts, 2 outdoor tennis courts, lap pool, state-of-the-art gymnasium and Four Seasons Spa. The Hotel boasts a Michelin One Star Cantonese restaurant, Jiang-Nan Chun, the botanical-inspired One-Ninety and polished One-Ninety Bar. Four Seasons Hotel Singapore is dedicated to perfecting the travel experience through continual innovation and the highest standards of hospitality. From elegant surroundings to authentic, highly personalised 24-hour service, the Hotel embodies a true home away from home for those who know and appreciate the best.','4.5','4/356','5894','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0e/9b/d8/62/jiang-nan-chun-main-dining.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','282.440 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (305,'Shangri-La Hotel, Singapore','22 Orange Grove Rd Orchard Road, Singapore 258350 Singapore','Be welcomed by Shangri-La Hotel\'s Singapore\'s Asian service from the heart, step into its striking lobby oasis and discover a world of luxurious indulgence. Nestled within 15 acres of tropical landscaped gardens, guests are warmly embraced by the hotel’s distinct service and smiles. A sanctuary in the heart of the city, this tropical hideaway provides a vibrant and diverse social scene, unparalleled culinary experiences and family facilities to indulge in the best of everything, or simply relax, unwind and let the world go by.','4.5','5/356','6736','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/12/be/2f/a0/lobby.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','251.440 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (306,'Oakwood Premier AMTD Singapore','6 Shenton Way Oue Downtown 1 #07-01, Singapore 068809 Singapore','Located in the heart of Singapore’s vibrant Central Business District, Oakwood Premier AMTD Singapore is a 268-unit hotel and serviced apartment offering a selection of the best in luxury living, style and design to cater to the needs of discerning international business and leisure travelers. Blending urban style with nature-inspired elements, the elegantly furnished and well-appointed studio, one- and two-bedroom apartments provide sophisticated travelers a high-quality living environment, tailored with all the luxuries of a hotel. Newly opened in 2017, Oakwood Premier AMTD Singapore was recently honored as ‘Best Serviced Residence in Asia-Pacific’ at the 2018 Business Traveller Asia-Pacific Awards and ‘Best Serviced Residence (Property Level)’ at the 29th Annual TTG Travel Awards 2018. for 2018 and 2019. With effect from 18 November 2019, Oakwood Premier OUE Singapore has been renamed to Oakwood Premier AMTD Singapore. The property continues to be operated by Oakwood, a leading provider of serviced apartments. As of June 2020, Oakwood Premier AMTD Singapore is certified SG Clean by National Environment Agency. The SG Clean quality mark, a premises-based sanitation and hygiene indicator is our unwavering commitment to guests by adhering to a rigorous sanitation and hygiene checklist to maintain high standards of public hygiene for licensed hotels in Singapore. Your safety and health matter to us and we will continually ensure you are in good hands during the stay.','5.0','3/356','242','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/3e/bc/af/pool.jpg?w=300&h=-1&s=1','194.104 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (307,'Amara Sanctuary Resort Sentosa','1 Larkhill Road, Sentosa Island 099394 Singapore\r\n','Amara Sanctuary Resort Sentosa is a 140-room boutique resort in Singapore nested within 3.8 hectares of secluded tropical gardens on the hillside of Sentosa’s popular Palawan Beach.A ten minute drive from the Central Business District on mainland Singapore, it is easily accessible for both business and leisure travellers.Winner of Singapore Tatler The Best of Singapore Awards 2010 to 2013 - Best Resort.Winner of Singapore Service Class Award 2012.Winner of AsiaOne People\'s Choice Awards 2009 - Best Resort.Winner of URA Architectural Heritage Awards 2007 - ','4.0','13/17','529','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0f/14/79/38/larkhill-suites.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','146.467 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (308,'PARKROYAL COLLECTION Pickering, Singapore','3 Upper Pickering Street, Singapore 058289 Singapore','PARKROYAL COLLECTION Pickering offers guests a luxury business hotel conveniently located at the gateway to Singapore’s central business district, near Raffles Place. Enjoy close proximity to key cultural, shopping and entertainment attractions. And take advantage of our spa, fitness centre, jogging path and pool – all conveniently located on the same floor.','4.5','26/356','4550','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/08/c1/ff/48/the-hotel--v8113879.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','226.607 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (309,'Studio M Hotel','No. 3 Nanson Road, Singapore 238910 Singapore','Studio M Hotel Singapore exudes avant-garde style and class in its offer of a great business stay or leisure getaway in the iconic entertainment precinct of Robertson Quay. Designed by Italian style maestro and architect, Piero Lissoni, it is the first fully loft-inspired Singapore hotel that also occupies a prime location in the city, within easy reach of both the Central Business District and the world famous Orchard Road.','3.5','252/356','2974','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/45/21/6a/exterior.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','130.198 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (310,'Carlton City Hotel Singapore','1 Gopeng Street, Singapore 078862 Singapore\r\n','Within a two-minute walk from Tanjong Pagar MRT station, Carlton City Hotel Singapore is conveniently located on Gopeng Street off Tanjong Pagar Road, along the fringes of Chinatown, Raffles Place and within the Central Business District. The hotel offers guests an upscale and stylish experience, resonating well with international business and leisure travellers. Designed by reputed leading international interior design company Hirsch Bedner Associates (HBA), the hotel exudes designer-conceived touches and furnishings from the grand marble lobby to its spacious guestrooms. With 29 floors and 386 guestrooms, the hotel is primed to be the preferred hotel for discerning business and leisure travellers.','4.5','49/356','1935','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/17/3f/03/c2/hotel-lobby.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','171.358 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (311,'Pan Pacific Singapore','7 Raffles Boulevard Marina Square, Singapore 039595 Singapore\r\n','Located in the heart of Marina Bay and Singapore\'s Central Business District, Pan Pacific Singapore provides newly-renovated rooms and suites with panoramic views of the city skyline. Linked via skybridge to three shopping malls and Suntec City Singapore International Convention and Exhibition Centre, guests will be surrounded by iconic attractions within walking distance including the ArtScience Museum, Gardens by the Bay, Marina Bay integrated resort and Esplanade - Theatres by the Bay. Leisure and business travellers will enjoy a superb choice of dining, entertainment and cultural atractions. Within the hotel, 6 signature award-winning restaurants, an outdoor swimming pool and 24-hour fitness centre offer options to dine and unwind at. The Promenade mrt station located within five minutes\' walking distance offers utmost convenience and connectivity to the city and a complimentary weekday shuttle bus operates around the Marina Bay Financial Centre route.','4.5','13/356','10692','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0a/a0/f4/56/atrium-lounge-lobby.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','207.392 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (312,'Hotel Bencoolen - Hong Kong Street','47 Hongkong Street Hotel Bencoolen @ Hongkong Street, Singapore 059685 Singapore','At Hotel Bencoolen, we offer international-standard accommodation with the personalized service of a boutique hotel, at affordable prices. Our properties are conveniently located in quiet alcoves, just minutes from key areas in Singapore. All of our 33 rooms are well-appointed with modern amenities and free Wi-Fi to ensure a comfortable stay for our guests.','4.0','1/89','360','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0a/53/eb/2e/hotel-bencoolen-building.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','164.685 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (313,'Orchard Hotel Singapore','442 Orchard Road, Singapore 238879 Singapore\r\n','We are delighted to update that Orchard Hotel Singapore has completed its latest phase of the enhancement, unveiling brand new areas of the hotel including reception, dining, meeting and event spaces as well as the Grand Deluxe rooms in the Orchard Wing. Located along Orchard Road, and just a short walk from the MRT station, Orchard Hotel Singapore features a half Olympic-size outdoor swimming pool, a life-size chessboard, and fully-equipped fitness centre. Its perfect location and choice offerings for business and leisure make for a stay secluded from the hustle of the busy city, whilst Singapore’s top shopping and entertainment options are available on its doorstep. Contemporary, yet classic in style, our 656 tastefully appointed Orchard road accommodation features modern conveniences and Chinese accents, allowing guests to feel truly at home. Amenities include flat-screen TVs with premium cable channels, rain showers and pillow menus, along with complimentary Wi-Fi.','4.5','22/356','643','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/17/48/8b/fb/lobby-orchard-hotel-singapore.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','165.330 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (314,'Hotel Bencoolen @ Bencoolen Street','47 Bencoolen Street Hotel Bencoolen, Singapore 189626 Singapore','A 3-star no frills hotel offering a choice of single, double, twin rooms to family rooms in the city area. Conveniently located with close proximity to the National Museum, Singapore Management University, National Academy of Fine Arts, School of The Arts, Bugis Street and Orchard Road. Churches, mosques, temples, shopping centres, convenience stores, restaurants and cafes are within walking distance. Public transportation such as MRT, buses and taxis are easily accessible.','3.5','214/356','706','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0a/89/c9/61/hotel-bencoolen-building.jpg?w=300&h=300&s=1','99.409 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (315,'The Great Madras','28, 30 & 32 Madras Street, Singapore 208422 Singapore','ON THE LITTLE RED DOT,\r\n\r\nIN LITTLE INDIA, SITS A LITTLE GREAT HOTEL.\r\n\r\nOF LITTLE OBJECTS THAT SPEAK OF TIME AND PLACE.\r\n\r\nOF LITTLE STORIES OF PEOPLE WHO HAVE MADE GREAT JOURNEYS,\r\n\r\nSEEN GREAT THINGS, AND LIVED GREAT LIVES.\r\n\r\nTHESE PEOPLE HAVE LEFT A LITTLE OF THEIR GREATNESS\r\n\r\nTO MAKE THE GREAT MADRAS, GREAT.THE GREAT MADRAS IS SMALL IN SIZE— JUST 35 ROOMS BUT IT IS GREAT ON ATTITUDE, PERSONALITY & SERVICE ','3.5','126/348','87','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/11/92/fd/fe/getlstd-property-photo.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','136.053 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (316,'30 Bencoolen','30 Bencoolen Street, Singapore 189621 Singapore','30 Bencoolen offers a cool, contemporary ambience in an ideal central location in the arts and cultural district. Relax in a warmly decorated room a short walk from top attractions in Singapore such as the landmark National Museum and Singapore Art Museum. Family rooms for up to 4 guests are available. You can enjoy casual all-day dining in our hip restaurant and gourmet coffees or chilled wines in the lounge bar. After a busy day, head up to the rooftop to unwind in the outdoor pool and spa tub. The hotel is a short stroll from 3 MRT stations. Bras Basah offers direct connections to Marina Bay’s striking, waterfront Esplanade – Theatres on the Bay, Suntec City Convention Centre and the Gardens by the Bay parks. Dhoby Ghaut sits near Plaza Singapura shopping centre, one of a host of upmarket malls on the famous Orchard Road shopping belt.','4.5','31/356','569','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/11/cb/42/81/hotel-facade.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','132.027 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
 (317,'Mandarin Orchard Singapore','333 Orchard Road, Singapore 238867 Singapore\r\n','Mandarin Orchard Singapore has been a landmark of Asian hospitality on world-renowned Orchard Road since 1971. The Hotel is preferred by discerning international travellers for its service excellence and prime location in the heart of Singapore’s most prominent shopping district. The hotel boasts some 1077 spacious guestrooms and suites that offer views of the city skyline from higher floors, and are designed with modern conveniences that cater to business travellers. Awaiting guests of the Meritus Club are bespoke amenities and privileged offerings—from detailed attention and personalised service by Meritus Ambassadors, to all-day refreshments served in the exclusive environment of the Meritus Club Lounge at Top of the M. Starring in the hotel’s vibrant lineup of restaurants is the all-time favourite Chatterbox, home of the legendary Mandarin Chicken Rice; Triple Three, a Japanese-inspired international buffet restaurant; and the highest Michelin-rated Chinese restaurant in Singapore since 2016, Shisen Hanten by Chen Kentaro. Right on the doorstep of Mandarin Orchard Singapore is Mandarin Gallery—a unique shopping destination featuring an exciting variety of luxury brands and boutique eateries. Mandarin Orchard Singapore offers over 30000 square feet of versatile meeting and function spaces backed by the dedicated service of Meeting and Event Specialists. The iconic hotel scored its eighth win as Best City Hotel-Singapore at the 30th Annual TTG Travel Awards and was also named Best Upscale Hotel-Singapore at the Travel Weekly Asia Readers\' Choice Awards 2017-2019. Mandarin Orchard Singapore and its restaurants have been awarded the SG Clean quality mark by Singapore Tourism Board and Enterprise Singapore. The mark is given after an assessment by a third-party auditor based on a sector-specific checklist of requirements for sanitation and hygiene standards within the premises.','4.0','83/356','12058','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/12/c0/d5/b1/orchard-link-side-facade.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','193.101 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Hotel','sg'),
