 (400,'Buddha Tooth Relic Temple and Museum','288 South Bridge Road, Singapore 058840 Singapore','The Buddha Tooth Relic Temple and Museum (BTRTM) was founded in 2002 by Venerable Shi Fazhao. It was registered by the Registrar of Societies in 20th February 2003, and as a charity under the Charities Act in 8th January 2004. The Temple is dedicated to the Maitreya Buddha, which means \'The Compassionate One\', and also called \'The Future Buddha\'. (A)WEEKLY FREE GUIDED TOUR: BTRTM is pleased to offer a 1 1/2 - 2 hrs long guided tour of the Temple every Saturdays at 2pm. The tour will be conducted free-of-charge in English by the temple\'s Volunteers guides. Limited slots are available per weekly session. Confirmed registration is based on first-come-first-serve basis. (B)DISCOVERING BUDDHISM: Shakyanmuni Buddha had gained insight into the truth, perfected the qualities of wisdom and compassion over 2560 years ago. His teachings develops clarity in minds, enables abilities to end suffering and finds lasting happiness. Buddha Tooth Relic Temple is carrying on the mission in offering \"Discovering Buddhism\' programme. \'Discovering Buddhism\' is a specially designed programme for participants to gain experiential taste of Chinese Mahayana Buddhist etiquette, Basic Buddhist teachings and Basic Meditation within a day. This English taught programme is suitable for both tourists who wish to learn more about Buddhism and experienced learners who needs a refresher. Participants will benefit from the interactive and engaging teaching led by Venerable Wu Xiang and Venerable Ru Zhi who have more than a decade experience teaching Buddhism and Meditation in different cultural settings! [Chinese Mahayana Buddhist Etiquette] Buddhist etiquette is an important part of every Buddhist life. It expresses religious sentiments to the Buddha, the Teacher (Monk or Nun) and promotes gracefulness in social interactions. This is also a mean of training in mindfulness in every action one is taking. [Basic Buddhist teachings] Buddhism has been transmitted over the past centuries because of its timeless and enduring message to the spiritual needs of man in finding true peace, happiness, and well-being. In this part of the programme, learn about the basic essential knowledge of Buddhism. [Basic Meditation] Buddhist have been practicing meditation in cultivating calm, focused and positive states of mind. Introductory of technique will be taught to enable the participants to learn practical tips on how to achieve a clearer state of mind and focus better. Things to take note : * Avoid wearing hats, shorts or revealing tops * The organizer reserves the right to cancel the tour due to unforeseen circumstances. In such instances, registrants will be notified via their mobile phones.','4.5','26/1012','6419','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/03/cd/dc/ac/buddha-tooth-relic-temple.jpg?w=200&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (401,'Marina Bay','Marina Boulevard, Singapore 018980 Singapore','This is definitely a great place to visit the view is incredible and it’s best to see the sun set n city lights come on we went back one night and wat he’d the laser show from across the bay it’s a good experience!','4.5','6/1012','12987','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0b/1c/10/7e/marina-bay-view-from.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (402,'Merlion Park','1 Fullerton Road One Fullerton Merlion Park, Singapore 049213 Singapore','Standing at 8.6 metres high and weighing 70 tonnes, the Merlion statue has a lion’s head and a fish’s body, and is housed here in this 2,500 square metre park.','4.0','57/1012','9546','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0a/80/e1/3f/photo0jpg.jpg?w=200&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (403,'Orchard Road','Singapore Singapore','Spanning almost 2.2 km, Orchard Road is a swanky, tree-lined one-way boulevard flanked by distinctive shopping malls and hotels. The shopping belt comprises nearly 800,000 sq m of shops and restaurants and promises to please any taste or budget with its iconic malls which boast the full works - from opulent brands to high street fashion, and from exclusive restaurants to fast food joints. It is a great street to shop, dine, stay, play, work, and live.','4.0','10/1012','13500','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/08/b7/cd/fd/retail-and-entertainment.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (404,'Clarke Quay','3 River Valley Road Clarke Quay Nearest Train Station: NE5 Clarke Quay MRT and DT20 Fort Canning Station, Singapore 179019 Singapore','Enjoy a River Cruise from Clarke Quay (Fort Canning jetty) to cruise along Singapore River and stop at (Eu Tong Seng Jetty / Bayfront North Jetty or Raffles Place Jetty.','4.5','48/1012','1012','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/24/78/e2/clarke-quay.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (405,'Haji Lane','21A Haji Lane 21A Haji Lane, Singapore 189214 Singapore','The burst of colors, the row of perfectly lined stores made for Instagram photos, quirky boutiques, street art and really hip bars and cafes make this a far more interesting place to hang out compared to the more...','4.0','54/1012','1036','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/03/64/c0/cb/haji-lane-for-boutique.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (406,'River Safari','80 Mandai Lake Road Singapore Zoological Gardens, Singapore 729826 Singapore','River Safari is Asia\'s first and only river-themed wildlife park inspired by the world\'s most iconic rivers. Witness some of the biggest, most endangered animals from these rivers, in lofty tanks and luscious walk-through exhibits! A must-see are giant pandas Kai Kai and Jia Jia in Southeast Asia\'s largest giant panda exhibit. Plus the world\'s largest freshwater aquarium themed after the Flooded Amazon Forest! The River is Calling...','4.0','75/1012','2985','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/15/82/eb/27/be-amazed-by-the-world.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','32.458 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (407,'Maxwell Food Centre','1 Kadayanallur Street, Singapore 069184 Singapore','Definitely try Zhen Zhen Porridge which serves mouth watering porridge cooked to perfection topped with all kinds of great ingredients.','4.0','55/1012','3268','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/11/24/ad/be/caption.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (408,'OCBC Skyway','18 Marina Gardens Drive Gardens By the Bay Gardens by the Bay, Singapore 018953 Singapore','For an Extra $8, you can take an elevator to go up the skyway and get a birds eye view of the super tree grove as well as the surroundings.','4.5','40/1012','562','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0b/15/64/ff/caption.jpg?w=200&h=200&s=1','19.917 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (409,'National Gallery Singapore','1 St. Andrew\'s Road #01-01 National Gallery Singapore, Singapore 178957 Singapore','Situated in the heart of Singapore’s Civic District, National Gallery Singapore oversees the largest public collection of modern art in Southeast Asia. Housed in two beautifully restored national monuments – City Hall and former Supreme Court – are impeccably curated exhibitions that reveal the region’s cultural legacy and art histories. Come visit the Gallery today and discover Singapore and Southeast Asia’s rich heritage through stunning modern art masterpieces.','4.5','33/1012','1266','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/11/ec/5b/45/national-gallery-singapore.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (410,'Asian Civilisations Museum','1 Empress Place Empress Place Building, Singapore 179555 SingaporeMap','The Asian Civilisations Museum is devoted to exploring the rich artistic heritage of Asia, especially the ancestral cultures of Singaporeans. Founded in 1993 and in its present building by the Singapore River since 2003, the museum traces its roots to the Raffles Museum, founded in the middle of the 19th century. ACM focuses on the many historical connections between the cultures of Asia, and between Asia and the world. Singapore’s history as a port city that brought people together from all over the world is used as a means of examining the history of Asia. Special exhibitions bring magnificent objects from around the world to our Singapore audience. Programmes like the annual River Nights encourage visitors to connect more closely with culture and the arts.','4.5','30/1012','2190','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/fc/53/a5/asian-civilisations-museum.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','4.331 krw','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (411,'The Southern Ridges','Alexandra Road Mount Faber Park; Telok Blangah Hill Park; or Kent Ridge Park, Singapore 099203 Singapore','Bridging the hills of Mount Faber Park, Telok Blangah Hill Park and Kent Ridge Park, the Southern Ridges combine invigorating exercise with spectacular views across Singapore.','4.5','22/1012','1163','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/a0/19/d8/forest-walk.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (412,'East Coast Park','Along East Coast Parkway and East Coast Park Service Road, Singapore 455486 Singapore','The city’s most popular stretch of beach always buzzes with activity – even when it’s not playing host to the wide spectrum of sporting events that grace its shores regularly, like the Singapore Marathon and Xtreme Championship.','4.5','43/1012','1208','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/19/0f/b9/07/west-coast-park.jpg?w=300&h=200&s=1','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (413,'The Helix Bridge','Linking between Marina Bay and Marina Centre, Singapore 038981 Singapore','Linking Marina Bay to Marina Centre, the Helix Bridge, is set to become Singapore’s next landmark. Located beside the Benjamin Sheares Bridge, alongside the vehicular Bayfront Bridge, it was officially opened on 24 April 2010 and is the world’s first curved bridge.','4.5','34/1012','2899','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/04/06/91/67/the-helix-bridge.jpg','0','Singapore','Singapore','Attractions','sg'),
 (414,'VUE Hotel Hou Hai, Beijing','No.9 Yangfang Alley, Xicheng District, Beijing 100009 China','VUE - Come as a guest, come back as a friend!\r\n\r\nVUE Hotel Hou Hai is the new upscale design boutique hotel in the centre of Beijing. This one-of-a-kind brand new hotel is located in the stunning surroundings of Houhai and offers an unforgettable staycation experience in a design combination of traditional Chinese architecture with contemporary and futuristic influences.\r\n\r\nThe Hotel\r\n\r\nA major adaptive-reuse exercise, the hotel comprises a series of quasi-historic buildings from the 1950s. Upon entering the hotel you will discover a series of landscaped gardens, a bakery café fronting the bustle of the hutongs, a signature restaurant in a warehouse, a rooftop bar overlooking the lake and over 80 rooms and suites, several with private gardens or with views overlooking the park or lake.\r\n\r\nThe hotel compound comprises a series of buildings with a variety of architectural styles and approaches. Although designed primarily in the Chinese vernacular, the different buildings span a range of ornamentation from highly decorative roof eaves, characterful gargoyles, sculptured balconies and latticed window frames, to pared-back jack roofs and plain brickwork wall finishes. This diverse collection is brought together by color and landscaping.\r\n\r\nAll the buildings are conceptually draped in attractive shades of gray, echoing the palette of the surrounding hutongs, upon which key architectural details have been highlighted in a contemporary gold patina.\r\n\r\nThe VUE property is designed around a central narrative inspired by its locale or culture. For VUE Houhai Beijing, the narrative drew inspiration from the lake and its animal inhabitants.\r\n\r\nThe Rooms\r\n\r\nBold, cutting-edge, surprising....that is how we describe the rooms at VUE Hotel. Beyond the contemporary aesthetic, every room is designed with your needs in mind.\r\n\r\nThe hotel offers 80 rooms fragmanted into 11 different room types. Every single type is unique and designed for a memorable stay.\r\n\r\nFrom the intelligent lighting system to the room-wide Bluetooth audio system, from the in-room coffee machine to the hypoallergenic, 600-thread-count sheets, comfort and convenience are always at the forefront. All guest rooms feature spacious bathrooms, fully stocked with L’Occitane products. Ancient history, modern convenience, and futuristic design come together in harmony for an unforgettable guest experience at VUE Hotel.\r\n\r\nOur Neighbourhood\r\n\r\nVUE Hotel is located in Beijing, in the Hutong district of Houhai. The hotel compound sits on the edge of the picturesque Houhai lake, and neighbours a verdant public park, as well as historic Hutong houses which are still used by local inhabitants today. Located along Houhai’s banks are a district of bars and vibrant cafes.\r\n\r\nThe hotel looks out onto Houhai lake, while Prince Gong’s Mansion and the Former Residence of Soong Ching-ling are within walking distance. The hutongs are best explored on foot or by bike or rickshaw — just like the locals do. Stunning attractions such as Tiananmen Square, the Forbidden City, Jingshan Park, and the Temple of Heaven, are easily accessible by car or public transport.','5.0','1/6125','865','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0f/87/98/44/getlstd-property-photo.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','253.682 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (415,'Shangri-La Hotel, Beijing','29 Zizhuyuan Road, Beijing 100089 China','Shangri-La Hotel, Beijing is located on Beijing’s idyllic west side. The hotel is a gateway to some of Beijing’s breathtaking historical sites such as Great Wall, Summer Palace, Fragrance Mountain, and many more. The hotel is also in the heart of the financial and technological district – Zhong Guan Cun and within close proximity to renowned universities with easy access to two subway lines and international airports.','5.0','2/6125','7033','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/3f/c7/1f/hotel-exterior.jpg?w=300&h=300&s=1','201.432 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (416,'Holiday Inn Express Beijing Badaling','No.1 Guishui North Street Yanqing District, Beijing 102100 China','Holiday Inn Express Beijing Jinyu Badaling is an international brand hotel chain managed by InterContinental Hotels Group. The hotel is carefully located in Yanqing District, northwest of Beijing. Yanqing District is the capital\'s ecological conservation development zone. The climate is cold in winter and cool in summer. Known as the summer capital of Beijing, it is relying on abundant ice and snow resources to build a \"city of ice and snow\"; it is also the venue of the 2019 Beijing World Horticultural Exposition and Beijing 2022. One of the three major regions of the Winter Olympics. The hotel is located in Jinyu Badaling Hot Spring Resort, No. 1 North Street, Gushui. The park is located in Jingquan Lake, with sparkling water and distant mountains and lakes. The natural environment is comfortable and pleasant. Strategic location, adjacent to the Jiangshuiquan Wetland Park with a total area of ​​500 acres; famous scenic spots gathered around, 5 km from the World Expo, 13.5 km from the Badaling Great Wall, 13.8 km from the Badaling Wildlife Park, 5.7 km from the Vanke Stone Jinglong Ski Resort, ancient cliff ruins 16.8 kilometers, 9 kilometers from Longqingxia Scenic Area. The hotel has 133 rooms with novel design and fashion, among which the courtyard, duplex and family room are the most distinctive. The hotel provides guests with free Chinese and Western buffet breakfast, high-speed Internet access, soft and hard pillows, a 24-hour business center, self-service laundry room and self-service vending machines. It is committed to creating a safer and more sensible living environment for global travelers who are away from home. Holiday Inn Express Beijing Jinyu Badaling is an ideal choice for your leisure vacation, team building and development training.','5.0','3/6125','431','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/4b/8c/b4/exterior.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','97.139 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (417,'InterContinental Beijing Sanlitun','No.1 South Sanlitun Road, Chaoyang District, Beijing 100027 China','InterContinental Beijing Sanlitun, a truly international brand with latest fashion design, conveniently located in the most stylish entertainment district in Beijing, with easy access to famous leisure and scenic spots, ideally for travelers and social connectors with an aspirational lifestyle. The iconic hotel suitably adjacent to Embassy and CBD areas, boasts the most contemporary rooms and suites, cosmopolitan dining options, and 1,500 square meters creating the largest meeting facility in the area, truly balance the dynamic life for business and leisure travelers.','5.0','4/6215','1604','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/18/08/0e/8e/restaurant.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','474.835 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (418,'The Bulgari Hotel Beijing','Building 2 Courtyard No. 8 Xinyuan South Road, Chaoyang District, Beijing 100027 China','With lush gardens extending to the riverside, and walkways alongside it, the hotel’s 119 Rooms and Suites, including the Bulgari Suite, are complemented by a 1500-square-metre BVLGARI SPA, 25-metre pool, private park, Il Ristorante Niko Romito (ONE STAR. THE MICHELIN GUIDE BEIJING 2020）, Il Bar, and a BVLGARI ballroom, establishing a new benchmark for enlightened luxury living and personalised services.','5.0','5/6125','1067','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/4c/93/40/exterior.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','457.679 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (419,'Shangri-La China World Summit Wing, Beijing','No.1 Jianguomenwai Avenue Upper Floors of China World Tower, Starting From 64/F, Beijing 100004 China','China World Summit Wing, Beijing comprises 278 guest rooms and suites, four designer restaurants, two bars and a lounge. Accommodations with guest room sizes averaging 65 square metres are the most spacious in the city. Rooms and suites come with double basins and connecting room or adjacent room options. The hotel also houses the city\'s highest spa retreat with CHI, The Spa - Shangri-La\'s signature spa brand - on level 77. Most of the city\'s attractions, such as the Forbidden City and Tiananmen Square, are within a 15-minute drive. All in-house guests have access to Resident\'s Foyer on level 64, with complimentary fruits, snacks coffee, tea, soft drinks served throughout the day, 2 hours use of meeting room per room per day and Happy Hour from 6pm to 8pm daily.','5.0','6/6125','2029','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/18/b3/17/b3/caption.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','345.894 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (420,'Hotel Eclat Beijing','9, DongDaQiao Road Chaoyang District, Beijing 100020 China\r\n','A gleaming glass pyramid envelopes Hotel Eclat which is part of the architecturally striking Parkview Green development in Fangcaodi with designer boutiques, restaurants and cinemas. Modern, light and wonderfully spacious, this all-suite boutique hotel has a fitness centre and a stunning contemporary art collection.This has to be one of the city’s most elegant hotels and the keyword here is privacy. The rooms are inordinately generous, many with a private terrace and some with their own pool. A truly astounding art collection includes pieces by Salvador Dali, Andy Warhol and Zeng Fangzhi.Our luxury Beijing accommodations are designed to surround you with style, but also equipped with the latest technology to meet the demands of today’s traveler -including fast and free Wi-Fi and high speed internet to help you stay connected to the world. 24-hour access to Éclat Lounge with complimentary breakfast buffet, all day light refreshments and a delicious selection of afternoon canapés. Complimentary Wi-Fi and broadband access. Panasonic massage chair. Separate rainforest shower and bathtub. Bang & Olufsen audio system. IPod/ iPhone dock. Oversized 3D LCD TV with Blu-Ray DVD. Access to CD and DVD library. LCD TV in bathroom. Exclusive Miller Harris London bathroom amenities. Complimentary Illy capsule coffee and Revolution Tea selection. Complimentary mini-bar, branded mineral water. In-room Bar with a full range of beverages and Riedel glassware.The joy of staying here is the accessibility to designer shopping and a wealth of restaurants. Located in the heart of the Embassy District, the hotel is also within easy reach of the major city attractions and after a busy day sightseeing, the clubs and bars of Sanlitun are virtually on the doorstep.Convenient location with shopping, restaurants on the doorstep, spacious accommodation, suites with private pool, superb art collection, fine dining.','5.0','7/6125','2152','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1b/0e/98/98/exterior.jpg?w=300&h=-1&s=1','275.711 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (421,'Shangri-La\'s China World Hotel','No. 1 Jianguomenwai Avenue Chaoyang District, Beijing 100004 China','China World Hotel, Beijing is ideally located in Beijing’s central business district (CBD) and is attached to the China World Mall. The hotel offers 584 guestrooms, 69 modern and comfortable residential units at China World Hotel Residences, as well as newly refurbished Horizon Club rooms and suites unveiled in January 2019. The hotel’s five restaurants and bars, Aria Restaurant and Bar, Summer Palace, Scene a Café, Lobby Lounge and the Sweet Spot, offer multiple dining choices. The Health Club features a heated indoor swimming pool and a gymnasium equipped with spacious exercise studios. The climbing treadwall and core-building surfing machine are new equipment designed to boost a workout experience. The hotel also provides exceptional meeting and event facilities, and an in-house wedding specialist offers all-in wedding service.','5.0','8/6125','6034','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/12/3e/43/20/cwtc-complex-photo.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','203.467 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (422,'EAST, Beijing','No.22 Jiuxianqiao Road, Chaoyang District, Beijing 100016 China','EAST, Beijing is a business hotel with a life. Located in INDIGO in the Jiangtai area and very close to Wangjing Business Park; Beijing Capital International Airport and the Central Business District are just 15 minutes away. With 2 restaurants, a bold new bar, pool and gym facilities, 17 hectares of landscaped parkland and the 798 Art Zone on its doorstep, EAST, Beijing lets you balance your work and your life.','5.0','9/6125','1477','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1a/9f/26/60/domain.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','108.092 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (423,'CHAO Sanlitun Beijing','No. 4 Workers\' Stadium East Road, Chaoyang District, Beijing 100027 China\r\n','The essence of contemporary high-end hospitality. Born as a hotel and matured as a hot spot for modern lifestyle, CHAO connects enthusiasts across to places, products, and possibilities. In the center of the city and the heart of Sanlitun (the most happening scene for fashion, entertainment and nightlife) our property features 180 rooms, two restaurants, a bar, a curated wine cellar, a comprehensive selection of whisky providing exquisite comfortable dinning, 15 000m2 of event spaces, 3000m2 of Art Centre with exhibition rooms, a private cinema, a 2000 books library and an art print studio. We endeavour in the protection of the environment with no single plastic policy, carbon free transportation and in health benefits with plant base dishes, low sugar and salt recipes and a well-equipped gymnasium. We aim to simplify and enhance the life of those who choose us in Beijing.','5.0','10/6125','1200','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0c/a2/87/30/hall.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','279.114 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (424,'Sunrise Kempinski Hotel, Beijing','No. 18A Yanshui Road, Yanqi Lake, Huairou District, Beijing 101407 China','Located alongside the picturesque Yanqi Lake with magnificent views of Yan Mountain, and the Mutianyu Great Wall. This new destination,Sunrise Kempinski Hotel, Beijng embodies the shape of therising sun and symbolises harmony, unity and infinity. The luxury hotel offers 306 guestrooms and suites with magnificent views of Yanqi Lake, mountains and greenery, six restaurants and bars, meeting facilities, Kempinski The Spa, and recreational facilities, fitness center with an indoor swimming pool, Kids Club, as well as outdoor activities','5.0','11/6125','1254','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/06/eb/41/5f/sunrise-kempinski-hotel.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','353.111 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
 (425,'Hotel Jen Beijing by Shangri-La','No.1 Jianguomenwai Street, Chaoyang District, Beijing 100004 China','Located in Beijing\'s Central Business District, Hotel Jen Beijing is part of the Shangri-La Group. The newly-built Hotel Jen Beijing is part of the fully integrated China World Complex, which includes premier malls, offices and restaurants. Centrally located in buzzing Guomao, the complex provides direct access to major subway lines for convenient trips to some of Beijing\'s top attractions. Hotel Jen Beijing offers young-at-heart travellers fuss-free service with a refreshing sense of adventure and puts the city right at their doorstep. Enjoy upcoming events, a lively gastropub Beersmith, a modern and vibrant all-day dining restaurant San Wu Tang, smart meeting space Prototype and a fitness centre Trainyard that will help keep the great feelings going! Check into more than a physical space; check into a new state of mind. Because whether you\'re in Beijing for business or a bit of shopping, we blur the line between work and play in an informal, fun and inspiring setting.','5.0','12/5126','1197','https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0f/48/de/59/beersmith-taproom.jpg?w=400&h=300&s=1','170.192 krw','Beijing','China','Hotel','cn'),
