 (504,'Mutianyu Great Wall','Mutianyu Village, Bohai Town, Huairou District, Beijing China','In 1368 AD, Mutianyu Great Wall was built by Xu Da who is the main general for Zhuyuanzhang in the Great Wall ruins of Northern Qi Dynasty. Linked to Gubeikou in the east and Juyongguan in the west,the section of the Great Wall is the military hub defensing of the capitalsince ancient times. There are several famous watchtowers such as Zhengguantai, Dajiaolou, Yingfeidaoyang,Jiankou and Beijingjie, which has profound historical and cultural values. Surrounded by the mountains, the Greening rate of the Great Wall reaches 98%, and its scenery is beautiful. Known for its gorgeous scenery, Mutianyu is one of the essence in the Great Wall of Ming Dynasty. Mutianyuhas the characteristics of the fresh air, sided embrasure, peculiar guards, intensive watchtowers, the strong feeling of three-dimensional and the existing of the inside and outside branch. The Closed Tram, Speed slide, the China dream stone sity, the Great Wall hotel, Yisonglou restaurant are constructed inthe tourist area, so its facilities and function are perfect.The tourist area was added to the national 5A scenic spot list by the National Tourism Administration of China in 2011. In June 28, 2014,the Mutianyu Great Wallintegrated tourism service area put into use. The integrated tourism service area, having service functions including a visitor center, the Great Wall Culture Exhibition Center, and catering and tourism souvenirs street,covers an area of 20 acres.In this way, Mutianyu Great Wall will provide a better travel experience for visitors.','5.0','1/1637','23765','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-m/1280/0f/bc/d2/18/caption.jpg','221.687 krw','Beijing','China','Attractions','cn'),
 (505,'Forbidden City-The Palace Museum','No.4 Jingshanqian Street, Dongcheng District, Beijing 100009 China','Consisting of more than 9,000 rooms and spread over 250 acres, this huge palace complex was built in the 15th century and later extensively renovated and restored during the Qing Dynasty in the 18th century','4.5','4/1637','14083','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/daodao/photo-s/01/e6/73/33/caption.jpg','9.627 krw','Beijing','China','Attractions','cn'),
 (506,'Summer Palace (Yiheyuan)','No.19 Xinjian Gongmen Road, Haidian District, Beijing 100080 China','The Summer Palace is the summer resort for the Qing dynasty\'s royal family.It is covered 3/4 with the water,the rest are hills and palaces.The Long corridor is the longest corridor in the world.From the eastern end ,Moon invited gate you can see it is like straight line ,then it\'s twisting and turning like in the wonderland.On the right side of the Long corridor ,it is a beautiful lake .','4.5','2/1637','15016','https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/01/f4/cb/d7/summer-palace.jpg','15.663 krw','Beijing','China','Attractions','cn'),
